ParameterString.description: Calculated barometric altitude [I030/130,I062/135 dependend on I062/080 SRC]
Barometric altitude more reliable? Y, N
Calculated geometric altitude [I030/130,I062/130 dependend on I062/080 SRC]
Day of message in posix time.
DATA SOURCE ID, is derived from table DS and its sub tables
COMMUNICATION LINE ID determines the origin of the record, see table COMMS
Raw Mode S MB Data (= BDS registers)
Mode of flight - Longitudinal acceleration: 0 = Constant Groundspeed, 1 = Increasing Groundspeed, 2 = Decreasing Groundspeed, 3 = Undetermined, see also X__SD_MOF_LONG [I030/200 LONGI, I062/200 LONG]
Mode of flight - Transversal acceleration: 0 = Constant Course, 1 = Right Turn, 2 = Left Turn, 3 = Undetermined, see also X__SD_MOF_TRANS [I030/200 TRANS, I062/200 TRANS]
Mode of flight - Vertical acceleration: 0 = Level Flight, 1 = Climb, 2 = Descent, 3 = Undetermined, see also X__SD_MOF_VERT [I030/200 LONGI, I062/200 LONG]
Message format as defined in X__SD_MSG_FMTS, contents shall be ASTERIX, Aircat 500, Alenia, FPS117, RAT31SL, RSRP, TRS22, RDIF, MADREC, EUROCONTROL, DDE, CD2, Ericsson
Is the source a multiple-data-source [Y] or single-data-source [N]
Calculated WGS84 track latitude position (low or high resolution) [I062/105 or I062/106]
Calculated Cartesian track X position (low or high resolution) [I030/110, I062/100 or I062/101]
Calculated Cartesian track Y position (low or high resolution) [I030/110, I062/100 or I062/101]
Calculated WGS84 track longitude position (low or high resolution) [I062/105 or I062/106]
Unique record id starting with 0 on every new recording
Recording time with accuracy of 1s; is stamped by the communication process
24 bit target address / aircraft address / Mode-S address
Time of Message / Time of Day (= ms since last midnight), [I030/020, I062/070]
C:Calculated, R:Recording time, N:From data, L:Local time transform
Y = End of track, N = Track is still alive
Track number [I030/050 SYSTEM TRACK NUMBER, I062/040]
